-- Nomura Hires Deutsche Bank's Grant Chamberlain to Head Australian Mergers
-- Angus Whitley
-- 2010-06-21T01:41:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/nomura-hires-deutsche-bank-s-grant-chamberlain-to-head-australian-mergers.html

          
          
             Nomura Holdings Inc. said it hired
former Deutsche Bank AG banker Grant Chamberlain as head of
mergers and acquisitions in Australia.  
 Chamberlain will be a Sydney-based managing director,
Nomura said in an e-mailed statement today. The Tokyo-based
brokerage also said James Land joined as head of fixed income
for Australia.  
          
          


  


        